<normalised orig="holie" auto="true">holy</normalised> Ghost, who <normalised orig="proceedeth" auto="true">proceeds</normalised> from<lb/>
the Father and the <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>Son*e</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised></corr>
                  </choice>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
<p>II.</p><lb/>
<sp who="a">
               <p>Q. Let <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> now come to our <normalised orig="selues" auto="true">selves</normalised>,<lb/>
and first tel me what is the natural estate<lb/>
of man?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. <normalised orig="Euerie" auto="true">Every</normalised> man is by nature dead<lb/>
in <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> as a loathsome carrion, or as<lb/>
a dead corps <normalised orig="lieth" auto="true">lies</normalised> rotting and <normalised orig="stincking" auto="true">stinking</normalised><lb/>
in the <normalised orig="graue" auto="true">grave</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. What is <normalised orig="Sinne" auto="true">Sin</normalised>?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. Any breach of the <normalised orig="Lawe" auto="true">Law</normalised> of<lb/>
GOD, if it <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised> no more but the least<lb/>
want of that which the <normalised orig="Lawe" auto="true">Law</normalised> <normalised orig="requireth" auto="true">requires</normalised>.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
               <p>Q. How many <normalised orig="sortes" auto="true">sorts</normalised> of <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> are<lb/>
there?<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="b">
               <p>A. <normalised orig="Sinne" auto="true">Sin</normalised> is either the corruption<lb/>
                  <pb n="8"/>
                  <lb/>
of nature, or any <normalised orig="euil" auto="true">evil</normalised> actions that <normalised orig="proceede" auto="true">proceed</normalised><lb/>
of it as <normalised orig="fruites" auto="true">fruits</normalised> thereof.<lb/>
               </p>
            </sp>
            <sp who="a">
