are <normalised orig="moued" auto="true">moved</normalised> &amp; stirred to that which is<lb/>
<normalised orig="euil" auto="true">evil</normalised> to embrace it, and they are <normalised orig="neuer" auto="true">never</normalised><lb/>
stirred <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> that which is good, <normalised orig="vnlesse" auto="true">unless</normalised><lb/>
it be to <normalised orig="eschewe" auto="true">eschew</normalised> it. Lastly, the members<lb/>
of the <normalised orig="bodie" auto="true">body</normalised> are the instruments<lb/>
                  <pb n="9"/>
                  <lb/>
and <normalised orig="tooles" auto="true">tools</normalised> of the <normalised orig="minde" auto="true">mind</normalised> for the execution<lb/>
